<TITLE> Fishermen capture 11 pirates on Meghna </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Bhola, June 08 (bdnews24.com)Fishermen captured 11 pirates in the river Meghna early on Monday. The detained pirates were later handed over to the Bhola Sadar Police Station. Fisherman Musa Miah told bdnews24.com the pirates attacked their trawlers while they were fishing. "We informed other fishermen around our trawler on the cell phone. When they arrived the pirates jumping into the river. "We managed to catch eleven pirates," Musa said. Bhola police chief Shahjahan Sheikh said all of the detainees were the residents of Ludua of Laxmipur district. Police recovered local-made arms from them, he said and added that the pirates had been active on the Meghna since the outset of the Hilsa-catching season. bdne
